1.00	E.ON_Kernkraft_GmbH	E.ON Kernkraft GmbH	E.ON Kernkraft GmbH is a subsidiary of E.ON and operates six nuclear power plants in Germany, employing about 2600 workers. It is located in Tresckowstraße 5, 30457 Hannover. Furthermore, it owns one third of the Brunsbüttel nuclear power plant which was shut down in 2007 because of a long history of malfunctions and as part of a nuclear power phase-out, the plant has since not been used.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/d/d3/Kernkraftwerk_Brunsb%C3%BCttel_-_Landseite.jpg/220px-Kernkraftwerk_Brunsb%C3%BCttel_-_Landseite.jpg
